Somebody recently asked what our alternative to war is when defending from terrorism. We decided to break things down as far as we possibly could. We tested this with a few conservatives and they actually said it makes sense and they agree. 

Our alternative is to stop fucking worrying about it. Law enforcement is doing a superb job of keeping us safe from terror attacks (led by foreign fighters). You have 1:20,000,000 odds of dying from terrorism, including domestic and overseas attacks. You're more likely to be killed by a bog bite. Seriously. You don't see dog attacks hitting the national news, do you? Slow down now. Seriously, slow down. Read this slowly. ***numbers matter***numbers matter***numbers matter*** You need to be worried about things that will actually kill you. Seriously. Our job is self-preservation. We need to be smart about it. We need to look at what is most likely to kill us. Again- most likely to kill us. Still with me? Focus on real threats and determine those threats based on numbers. 1-7 will die of cancer. Ok, work out and eat healthier- stop smoking too. 1-100 from car accidents -ok- why the fuck isn't the media talking about this? 1-100? That's a bunch of us. I want some more cops on the road. I want safer cars and safer highways. I want a war on highway safety! Boom, my family and I are statistically much safer. Still with me? Next. 1:83,000 will die from lightning. Hmm. Should I be more worried about lightning based on that number? That's only 1 person out of the largest packed NFL stadium...seriously, that's a small number, right? So, nah, I'm not really worried about lightning. I'll still run to my car in a storm. I don't want a politician telling me to be very very afraid of lightning. Could you imagine if they tried? They would look ridiculous, wouldn't they? Imagine a whole GOP debate about lightning. Ok next we'll jump to terrorism. 1:20,000,000 will die from terrorism in their lifetimes (based on the past decade). That's 1 person, only 1, from about 250 packed NFL stadiums! Do you realize how small that is? Compare it back to the lightning (1 will die out of a packed stadium). It's really small. Infinitesimal. Hopefully you see now. You have better things to worry about if you want self-preservation. I want real safety measures. I want a 5 trillion dollar war on cancer. I want a trillion dollars spent on upgrading auto and highway safety. Fuck worrying about terrorism. The FBI and CIA have it mostly under control. We had one big slip-up on 9/11. They were mostly from Saudi Arabia and they trained in Florida. Florida. Seriously, their flight training was in Florida. If they can come from friendly countries, as welcomed guests, and train in Florida, then we sure as shit would be wasting time putting boots on the ground in a bunch of other countries. We still couldn't stop the next 9/11 with any amount of bombing, because there's a good chance they are from Saudi Arabia, who is our close friend/ally, and training in Florida. Please understand that numbers are important and they are a great way to better understand life and strengthen the human race. Fuck this deceptive media and the oligarchy that owns them.
